{"lemma":"قَوْسٌ","slug":"قَوْسٌ","root":"ق.#.س","root_slug":"ق-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-_-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36409"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be/become bent/curved"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to form or make a curved shape"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bend, to curve, to write"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bow, curve, twist"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bow, arch, vault"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"parenthesis, bracket"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ugaritic 𐎖𐎌𐎚 (qšt), Akkadian 𒄑𒉼 (qaštum), Hebrew קֶשֶׁת (qéšeṯ), Ge'ez ቀስት (ḳäst), ቀሥት (ḳäśt), ቀስተም (ḳästäm), ቀስታም (ḳästam), Amharic ቀስት (ḳäst), Tigrinya ቀስቲ (ḳästi), Tigre ቀሽ (ḳäš)."},"ipa":["/qa.wi.sa/","/qaw.wa.sa/","/qaws/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36409","headword_ar":"قَوْسٌ","root":"qws","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing, well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one shoots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) of the fem. gender: (IAmb, M, Msb:) or masc. and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2575},{"kind":"text","text":"fem.: (S, Msb:) or sometimes masc.: (A, K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqowaAsN","text_ar":"اَقْوَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoyaAsN","text_ar":"اَقْيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, and so in some copies of the K, in the place of the former,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being interchangeable with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisiY~N","text_ar":"قِسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwuwsN","text_ar":"قُوُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) which is not used, (TA,) of the neasure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) first changed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusuw~N","text_ar":"قُسُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of he measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwEN","text_ar":"فُلُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisiY~N","text_ar":"قِسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filiyEN","text_ar":"فِلِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSiY~N","text_ar":"عِصِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusiY~N","text_ar":"قُسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Sgh, K,) from the same original, (TA,) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSiY~N","text_ar":"عُصِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyaAsN","text_ar":"قِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAmb, S, A, Msb, K,) which is more agreeable with analogy than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qsY~","text_ar":"قسىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The dim. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosN","text_ar":"قُوَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAmb, M, Msb, K,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to rule, as the word is fem., (M, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosapN","text_ar":"قُوَيْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAmb, Msb, K,) sometimes: (IAmb, Msb:) or the former accord. to those who make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qws","text_ar":"قوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be masc., (S,) and the latter accord. to those who make it to be fem. (S, Msb.) It is prefixed to another word to give it a special signification. Thus you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu nabolK","text_ar":"قَوْسُ نَبْلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An Arabian bow."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu nu$~aAbK","text_ar":"قَوْسُ نُشَّابٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Persian bow."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu HusobaAnK","text_ar":"قَوْسُ حُسْبَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow for shooting a certain kind of short arrows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu julaAhiqK","text_ar":"قَوْسُ جُلَاهِقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cross-bow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu nadofK","text_ar":"قَوْسُ نَدْفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow for loosening and separating cotton"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yamud~u qawosahu A^aHadN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يَمُدُّ قَوْسَهُ اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one, no one will pull his bow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e., (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no one will vie with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compete with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramawonaA Eano qawosK waAHidK","text_ar":"رَمَوْنَا عَنْ قَوْسٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapK","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) [lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They shot at us from one bow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they were unanimous against us;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a proverb denoting agreement. (Mgh.) [In the Msb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramawohumo","text_ar":"رَمَوْهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapK","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayori quwayosK sahomFA","text_ar":"خَيْرِ قُوَيْسٍ سَهْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K; except that in the L and K, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwys","text_ar":"قويس"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosK","text_ar":"قَوْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of the best of a little bow, as an arrow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one of the best arrows of a little bow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra xayora","text_ar":"صَارَ خَيْرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosK sahomFA","text_ar":"قُوَيْسٍ سَهْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became the best of a little bow, as an arrow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became the best arrow of a little bow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a proverb [See Arab. Prov. i. 718] applied to him who has become mighty after being of mean condition: (A:) or to him who opposeth thee and then returns to doing what thou likest. (A, K.) [Hence also the phrase in the Kur, liii. 9,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fakaAna qaAba qawosayoni","text_ar":"فَكَانَ قَابَ قَوْسَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he was at the distance of two Arabian bows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two cubits"},{"kind":"text","text":"[this is app. an explanation by one who holds"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAba qawosayoni","text_ar":"قَابَ قَوْسَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAbaYa qawosK","text_ar":"قَابَىَ قَوْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (K:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAbaYo qawosK","text_ar":"قَابَىْ قَوْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the distance of the measure of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two portions between the part of a bow that is grasped by the hand and each of the curved extremities."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwb","text_ar":"قوب"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawosu","text_ar":"القَوْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Sign of Sagittarius;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAmiY","text_ar":"الرَّامِى"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the signs of the zodiac;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ninth thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu quzaHa","text_ar":"قَوْسُ قُزَحَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rainbow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the two words are inseparable. (TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qzH","text_ar":"قزح"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosu Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"قَوْسُ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bent, part of the back of a man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqowaAsu AlbaEiyir","text_ar":"اَقْوَاسُ البَعِيِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The anterior ribs of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b7-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What remains, of dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receptacle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jul~ap","text_ar":"جُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the bottom thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sides thereof, like a bow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or, accord. to Zeyd Ibn-Kuthweh, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fourth part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jul~ap","text_ar":"جُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of dates; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rizomapN","text_ar":"رِزْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rzm","text_ar":"رزم"},{"kind":"text","text":":) in this sense, also, it is fem.: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of dates collected together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA in the present art.)       -A2-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cubit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) sometimes used in this sense: (S:) because a thing is measured ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuqaAsu","text_ar":"يُقَاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") with it. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","M","TA","IAmb","Msb","S","Fr","Sgh","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}